1858年 内战爆发两年前

9
00:03:46,319 --> 00:03:49,363
德州某地

10
00:03:54,319 --> 00:03:56,863
等等 有情况
Whoa.

11
00:04:03,161 --> 00:04:04,329
吁
Whoa.

12
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:21,971
乌漆麻黑的谁在那鬼鬼祟祟?
Who's that stumblin' around in the dark?

13
00:04:22,138 --> 00:04:25,934
说明你的来意 不然就准备挂彩吧!
State your business or prepare to get winged!

14
00:04:26,100 --> 00:04:28,686
别冲动 先生们
Calm yourselves, gentlemen.

15
00:04:28,853 --> 00:04:31,189
我并无恶意
I mean you no harm.

16
00:04:31,356 --> 00:04:36,194
我只是个疲倦的旅人 停下 孩子
I'm simply a fellow weary traveler. Whoa, boy.

17
00:04:37,528 --> 00:04:39,197
寒冷的晚上好 先生们
Good cold evening, gentlemen.

18
00:04:39,364 --> 00:04:41,699
我在寻找一对奴隶商人
I'm looking for a pair of slave traders

19
00:04:41,866 --> 00:04:43,534
他们自称是斯派克兄弟
that go by the name of the Speck Brothers.

20
00:04:43,701 --> 00:04:45,536
请问是否是阁下?
Might that be you?

21
00:04:46,913 --> 00:04:49,666
- 谁想知道?  - 嗯 我想
- Who wants to know?  - Well, I do.

22
00:04:49,832 --> 00:04:51,709
我是金·舒尔茨医生 这是我的坐骑 小德
I'm Dr. King Schultz. This is my horse, Fritz.

23
00:04:52,961 --> 00:04:56,464
- 什么医生?  - 牙医
- What kinda doctor?  - Dentist.

24
00:04:56,631 --> 00:04:58,424
请问你们是斯派克兄弟吗?
Now, are you the Speck Brothers?

25
00:04:58,591 --> 00:05:01,386
你们是在格林维尔奴隶卖场买下他们的吗?
And did you purchase those men at the Greenville slave auction?

26
00:05:01,552 --> 00:05:04,138
- 是又怎样?  - 那我就有要事相商
- So what?  - So I wish to parley with you.

27
00:05:04,305 --> 00:05:07,642
- 说人话  - 喔 对不起
- Speak English.  - Oh, I'm sorry.

28
00:05:07,809 --> 00:05:10,019
请原谅 那并非我的母语
Please forgive me. It is a second language.

29
00:05:10,186 --> 00:05:13,481
目前 你手里这些存货 我深信里面
Now, amongst your inventory, I've been led to believe,

30
00:05:13,648 --> 00:05:16,067
一定有我需要的货色
is a specimen I'm keen to acquire.

31
00:05:16,234 --> 00:05:17,694
好啊 你们这些可怜的小鬼们!
Hello, you poor devils!

32
00:05:19,028 --> 00:05:21,614
你们之中谁曾经是
Is there one amongst you who was formerly a resident

33
00:05:21,781 --> 00:05:25,076
卡鲁肯农场的人?
of the Carrucan plantation?

34
00:05:25,827 --> 00:05:28,037
我是卡鲁肯农场来的
I'm from the Carrucan plantation.

35
00:05:29,664 --> 00:05:31,040
说话的人在哪?
Who said that?

36
00:06:18,254 --> 00:06:19,630
你叫什么名字?
What's your name?

37
00:06:23,801 --> 00:06:25,678
姜戈
Django.

38
00:06:25,845 --> 00:06:28,598
那我找的就是你了
Then you are exactly the one I'm looking for.

39
00:06:30,475 --> 00:06:32,685
你知道布里托兄弟是谁吗?
Do you know who the Brittle Brothers are?

40
00:06:36,314 --> 00:06:37,315
谁?
Who are they?

41
00:06:39,734 --> 00:06:41,360
大约翰
Big John.

42
00:06:42,153 --> 00:06:43,488
埃利斯
Ellis.

43
00:06:44,906 --> 00:06:48,826
罗杰 有时候也叫做小罗
Roger. Sometime they call him Lil Raj.

44
00:06:50,203 --> 00:06:52,413
他们都曾是卡鲁肯农场的监工
They was overseers at the Carrucan plantation.

45
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:53,664
他们走了
Not anymore.

46
00:06:56,751 --> 00:06:57,794
告诉我...
Tell me...

47
00:06:58,377 --> 00:07:01,172
如果你再遇到那三位
if you were to see any of these three gentlemen again,

48
00:07:01,339 --> 00:07:04,008
- 你能认出他们吗?  - 嘿
- would you recognize them?  - Hey.

49
00:07:04,175 --> 00:07:06,636
- 别这么跟他说话  - 怎么说?
- Stop talkin' to him like that.  - Like What?

50
00:07:06,803 --> 00:07:08,346
就你这么说
Like that.

51
00:07:08,513 --> 00:07:10,807
我的好兄弟 我只是想核定...
My good man, I'm simply trying to ascertain...

52
00:07:10,973 --> 00:07:13,017
说人话 该死的
Speak English, goddamn it.

53
00:07:13,184 --> 00:07:14,936
都冷静点
Everybody calm down.

54
00:07:15,103 --> 00:07:18,815
我只是个顾客 来做一笔买卖
I'm simply a customer trying to conduct a transaction.

55
00:07:18,981 --> 00:07:21,984
我不在乎 不卖 你走吧
I don't care. No sale. Now, off with ya.

56
00:07:22,151 --> 00:07:25,154
别开玩笑了 他们当然是待售的
Don't be ridiculous. Of course they're for sale.

57
00:07:25,988 --> 00:07:27,448
好狗不挡路
Move it.

58
00:07:27,615 --> 00:07:32,537
我的好兄弟 你这是摆个舞枪弄棒的姿势呢
My good man, did you simply get carried away with your dramatic gesture

59
00:07:32,703 --> 00:07:36,499
还是要动真枪威胁我?
or are you pointing your weapon at me with lethal intention?

60
00:07:37,583 --> 00:07:39,460
再给你一次机会 娘炮
Last chance, fancy pants.

61
00:07:40,878 --> 00:07:43,214
哦 好吧
Oh, very well.

62
00:08:11,993 --> 00:08:14,412
抱歉 射杀了你的牲口
I'm sorry to put a bullet in your beast,

63
00:08:14,579 --> 00:08:16,497
我是怕你还没三思
but I didn't want you to do anything rash

64
00:08:16,664 --> 00:08:18,958
就冲动行事
before you had a moment to come to your senses.

65
00:08:19,125 --> 00:08:22,545
你个狗娘养的!
You goddamn son of a bitch!

66
00:08:22,712 --> 00:08:25,506
- 你杀了罗斯科!  - 好吧...
- You shot Roscoe!  - Well...

67
00:08:25,673 --> 00:08:27,383
- 你还杀了小杰!  - 别急着下定论
- And you killed Ace! -No. No. No.

68
00:08:27,550 --> 00:08:30,219
我杀你哥也是出于自卫
I only shot your brother once he threatened to shoot me.

69
00:08:30,386 --> 00:08:33,222
而且我有... 一 二 三 四...
And I do believe I have... one, two, three, four...

70
00:08:33,389 --> 00:08:36,350
五名目击证人可以佐证
five witnesses who can attest to that fact.

71
00:08:36,517 --> 00:08:39,395
- 腿疼爆了!  - 必然的
- Damn leg's busted!  - No doubt.

72
00:08:39,562 --> 00:08:42,106
好了 请你尽量不要鬼哭狼嚎
Now, if you could keep your caterwauling down to a minimum,

73
00:08:42,273 --> 00:08:45,610
我想最后再问小姜戈几个问题
I'd like to finish my line of inquiry with young Django.

74
00:08:49,614 --> 00:08:53,075
- 天杀的我靠!  - 接着我刚说的...
- God-fuckin'-damn it!  - As I was saying...

75
00:08:53,242 --> 00:08:56,954
要是你再看见布里托兄弟你能认出他们吗?
if you were to see the Brittle Brothers again, you could recognize 'em?

76
00:08:57,622 --> 00:08:59,332
能
Yeah.

77
00:08:59,498 --> 00:09:00,791
成交!
Sold American!

78
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:04,921
那 斯派克先生? 斯派克? 小姜戈要多少钱?
So, Mr. Speck? Mr. Speck? How much for young Django here?

79
00:09:10,218 --> 00:09:12,845
那个大铁块是最恼人的了
That iron is nasty business.

80
00:09:18,059 --> 00:09:20,186
对了 你能帮我拿一下吗?
Oh, could you hold this for a moment?

81
00:09:22,313 --> 00:09:23,814
谢谢你 姜戈?
Thank you. Django?

82
00:09:23,981 --> 00:09:25,858
上马
Get up on that horse.

83
00:09:26,025 --> 00:09:27,818
还有 要是我是你
Also, if I were you,

84
00:09:27,985 --> 00:09:31,989
我就拿上那个死斯派克身上的大衣
I'd take that winter coat the dear departed Speck left behind.

85
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:50,007
黑鬼! 你敢动我哥的大衣
Nigger! Don't you touch my brother's coat.

86
00:10:00,685 --> 00:10:05,606
他妈的! 疼!
Goddamn it! Oh!

87
00:10:07,275 --> 00:10:12,446
一百... 一十... 二十...
One hundred... ten... 20...

88
00:10:12,613 --> 00:10:14,448
五块...
and five...

89
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:16,867
这是小姜戈的
for young Django here.

90
00:10:17,034 --> 00:10:19,203
既然你留着也没什么用
And since he won't be needing it anymore,

91
00:10:19,370 --> 00:10:21,872
我想连你哥的老马一并买下
I'd like to purchase your brother's nag.

92
00:10:22,581 --> 00:10:27,545
还有 斯派克先生 我恐怕还需要一张卖身契
Also, Mr. Speck, I'm afraid I will require a bill of sale.

93
00:10:27,712 --> 00:10:29,297
你有吗?
Do you have one?

94
00:10:29,463 --> 00:10:32,383
去死吧 牙医
You go to hell, dentist.

95
00:10:32,550 --> 00:10:34,552
我猜就没有
I thought not.

96
00:10:34,719 --> 00:10:38,222
别担心 我是有备而来
No worries. I come prepared.

97
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,145
谢谢
Thank you.

98
00:10:44,312 --> 00:10:47,898
就用这个当契约吧
This will serve nicely as a bill of sale.

99
00:11:00,244 --> 00:11:01,245
吁
Whoa.

100
00:11:05,416 --> 00:11:08,878
至于你们这些可怜的小鬼
Now, as to you poor devils.

101
00:11:09,045 --> 00:11:14,091
如此 就我看来 该考虑下一步做什么了
So, as I see it, when it comes to the subject of what to do next,

102
00:11:14,258 --> 00:11:17,094
现在是各位做出选择的时候了
you gentlemen have two choices.

103
00:11:17,261 --> 00:11:22,391
一条路是 我走之后 你们把活的那个斯派克从那牲口身下拽出来
One: Once I'm gone, you could lift that beast off the remaining Speck,

104
00:11:22,558 --> 00:11:24,477
然后把他抬到最近的小镇
then carry him to the nearest town.

105
00:11:24,643 --> 00:11:28,230
就是说得往回走大概至少37英里
Which would be at least 37 miles back the way you came.

106
00:11:28,397 --> 00:11:34,070
第二条路 你们可以把镣铐解开 拿上那把枪
Or two: You could unshackle yourselves, take that rifle,

107
00:11:34,236 --> 00:11:36,781
照着他脑袋上来一枪 然后把他倆的尸骨深埋
put a bullet in his head, bury the two of them deep,

108
00:11:36,947 --> 00:11:40,493
然后找个更开化的地方扎根
and then make your way to a more enlightened area of this country.

109
00:11:41,577 --> 00:11:42,745
供君选择
Choice is yours.

110
00:11:42,912 --> 00:11:47,291
对了 考虑到你们识星象的几率略低
Oh, and on the off chance there are any astronomy aficionados amongst you,

111
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:50,461
北极星在那边
the North Star is that one.

112
00:11:51,921 --> 00:11:55,091
拜拜啦
Ta-ta. 

113
00:12:09,897 --> 00:12:13,984
等等 小伙子们 我们可以谈谈!
Now wait a minute, fellas. Let's talk about this!

114
00:12:17,613 --> 00:12:21,033
你们得讲讲道理!
You gotta be reasonable in a situation like this!

115
00:12:22,493 --> 00:12:25,496
我不是坏人 我只是本分地工作!
I'm not a bad guy. I'm just doin' my job!

116
00:12:25,663 --> 00:12:29,250
蓝莓兄 我最后一个苹果不也给了你吗?
Blueberry, didn't I give you my last apple?

117
00:12:29,417 --> 00:12:32,378
这样吧 孩子们 带我去埃尔帕索城看大夫
Tell you what, boys: Take me to the doc in El Paso,

118
00:12:32,545 --> 00:12:34,588
我就放你们自由
I'll get you your freedom.

119
00:12:34,755 --> 00:12:38,509
不 别 求你们了...
No. No, please...

120
00:12:54,755 --> 00:12:58,509
德州 多特里

121
00:13:23,846 --> 00:13:25,222
好啦 听着
All right, now.

122
00:13:25,389 --> 00:13:27,391
这个今天晚上吃两片...
I'd like you to take two of these tonight...

123
00:13:27,558 --> 00:13:29,768
然后明早...
and then in the morning...

124
00:13:31,896 --> 00:13:33,689
那匹马上有个黑鬼
That's a nigger on a horse.

125
00:13:59,298 --> 00:14:01,091
他们都在看什么?
What's everybody staring at?

126
00:14:01,258 --> 00:14:03,761
他们从来没见过骑着马的黑鬼
They ain't never seen no nigger on a horse before.

127
00:14:16,065 --> 00:14:17,066
吁
Whoa.

128
00:14:27,117 --> 00:14:29,119
早安 老板!
Good morning, innkeeper!

129
00:14:30,454 --> 00:14:32,915
给我们两个疲倦的旅人来两杯啤酒
Two beers for two weary travelers.

130
00:14:33,082 --> 00:14:34,833
现在天色还早吧
It's still a bit early.

131
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,419
我们一个小时之后才开门
We won't be open for another hour.

132
00:14:37,586 --> 00:14:39,421
那时候 我们才提供早餐
By then, we'll be servin' breakfast.

133
00:14:39,588 --> 00:14:45,010
等等 等等 等等... 你这他妈的干什么呢?
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa... what the hell you think you're doing, boy?

134
00:14:45,177 --> 00:14:47,263
把那黑鬼赶出去!
Get that nigger outta here!

135
00:14:50,808 --> 00:14:54,812
- 救命啊! 出大事啦!  - 老板!
- Help! Help!  - Innkeeper!

136
00:14:54,979 --> 00:14:58,148
记得 去叫警长 别叫成司法官了
Remember, get the sheriff, not the marshal.

137
00:14:58,315 --> 00:15:00,192
警长! 救命啊!
Sheriff! Help!

138
00:15:00,359 --> 00:15:01,986
哎
Alas.

139
00:15:03,362 --> 00:15:05,906
我们现在得自己动手了 
Now we must act as our own bartender.

140
00:15:08,325 --> 00:15:10,077
坐下吧 孩子
Sit down, my boy.

141
00:15:19,753 --> 00:15:22,631
你是哪门子的牙医?
What kind of dentist are you?

142
00:15:23,465 --> 00:15:28,053
别看那个小车 其实我有五年没出诊了
Despite that cart, I haven't practiced dentistry in five years.

143
00:15:32,683 --> 00:15:35,978
但现在 我已经改行了...
But these days, I practice a new profession...

144
00:15:38,188 --> 00:15:39,565
做赏金猎人
bounty hunter.

145
00:15:46,155 --> 00:15:47,990
你知道什么叫赏金猎人吗?
Do you know what a bounty hunter is?

146
00:15:48,699 --> 00:15:49,742
不知道
No.

147
00:15:49,908 --> 00:15:51,118
好吧...
Well...

148
00:15:52,745 --> 00:15:56,874
就跟奴隶买卖一样 拿人命换钱
the way the slave trade deals in human lives for cash,

149
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,376
赏金猎人是拿尸首换钱
a bounty hunter deals in corpses.

150
00:15:59,543 --> 00:16:01,754
帽子
Hat.

151
00:16:05,507 --> 00:16:07,051
干杯
Prost.

152
00:16:15,225 --> 00:16:17,895
州里提名悬赏人头
The state places a bounty on a man's head.

153
00:16:18,062 --> 00:16:20,731
我追踪 锁定 然后了结他
I track that man, I find that man, I kill that man.

154
00:16:20,898 --> 00:16:24,860
了结他之后 我再把他的尸首运回去鉴定
After I've killed him, I transport that man's corpse back to the authorities.

155
00:16:25,027 --> 00:16:27,738
有时说比做可容易多了
Sometimes that's easier said than done.

156
00:16:27,905 --> 00:16:30,699
我把尸首交给当局 确定一下
I show that corpse to the authorities, proving yes, indeed,

157
00:16:30,866 --> 00:16:32,576
我亲手杀死了他
I truly have killed him,

158
00:16:32,743 --> 00:16:35,746
然后当局再付给我相应的赏金
at which point the authorities pay me the bounty.

159
00:16:35,913 --> 00:16:39,249
所以 就像奴隶买卖 人头换金钱
So, like slavery, it's a flesh for cash business.

160
00:16:40,876 --> 00:16:41,877
什么是赏金?
What's a bounty?

161
00:16:45,673 --> 00:16:47,132
就是奖赏
It's like a reward.

162
00:16:47,299 --> 00:16:50,678
你杀人? 然后他们给你奖赏?
You kill people? And they give you a reward?

163
00:16:50,844 --> 00:16:52,721
某些人 对
Certain people, yeah.

164
00:16:52,888 --> 00:16:54,014
坏人?
Bad people?

165
00:16:54,181 --> 00:16:58,143
对! 他们越坏 奖赏越多
Ah! Badder they are, bigger the reward.

166
00:16:58,310 --> 00:17:00,604
然后我就找上了你
Which brings me to you.

167
00:17:00,771 --> 00:17:05,025
我必须承认 对你呢 我有点进退两难
And I must admit, I'm at a bit of a quandary when it comes to you.

168
00:17:05,192 --> 00:17:07,611
一方面 我鄙视奴隶制度
On one hand, I despise slavery.

169
00:17:07,778 --> 00:17:10,906
另一方面 我实在需要你的帮助
On the other hand, I need your help.

170
00:17:11,073 --> 00:17:14,451
如果你不持反对意见的话 那就太好了
If you're not in a position to refuse, all the better.

171
00:17:15,327 --> 00:17:17,996
所以 那时 我只能借奴隶买卖
So, for the time being, I'm gonna make this slavery malarkey

172
00:17:18,163 --> 00:17:20,374
达到我自己的目的
work to my benefit.

173
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:25,212
不过 我已经说过了 我深感内疚
Still, having said that, I feel guilty.

174
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:32,136
因此 我想和你订个君子协议
So, I would like the two of us to enter into an agreement.

175
00:17:39,184 --> 00:17:41,019
我在找布里托兄弟
I'm looking for the Brittle Brothers.

176
00:17:45,691 --> 00:17:47,025
但是 就算我再努力
However, at this endeavor,

177
00:17:47,192 --> 00:17:52,322
不知对方相貌 我显然占了下风
I'm at a slight disadvantage insofar as I don't know what they look like.

178
00:17:53,574 --> 00:17:56,452
但是你认得他们 对吧?
But you do. Don't ya?

179
00:17:56,618 --> 00:17:58,829
我是认得他们的长相
I know what they look like all right.

180
00:17:58,996 --> 00:18:02,499
好 我们就此协定
Good. So here's my agreement.

181
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:06,086
- 你陪同我 直到我们找到他们  - 我们去哪找?
- You travel with me until we find them.  - Where we goin'?

182
00:18:06,253 --> 00:18:08,881
我听说他们其中至少两个在加特林堡做监工
I hear at least two of them are overseeing up in Gatlinburg,

183
00:18:09,047 --> 00:18:11,216
但是我没有确切地点
but I don't know where.

184
00:18:11,383 --> 00:18:15,679
所以我们要走遍加特林堡的农场去找
That means we visit every plantation in Gatlinburg till we find 'em.

185
00:18:15,846 --> 00:18:21,101
找到他们之后 你把他们指认出来 然后我来了结他们
And when we find them, you point them out, and I kill them.

186
00:18:22,144 --> 00:18:25,522
你只要这么做 我就答应给你自由
You do that, I agree to give you your freedom,

187
00:18:25,689 --> 00:18:29,818
每个人头分你25块 一共75块
$25 per Brittle Brother. That's $75.

188
00:18:29,985 --> 00:18:33,697
果然不出所料 警长来了
And, as if on cue, here comes the sheriff.

189
00:18:41,455 --> 00:18:46,960
好啦 孩子们 闹够了吧 出来吧
OK, boys. Fun's over. Come on out.

190
00:18:49,588 --> 00:18:54,176
好啦 都冷静
All right, folks, calm down.

191
00:18:55,219 --> 00:18:56,929
都该干啥干啥去
Go about your business.

192
00:18:57,721 --> 00:19:00,098
这俩小鬼很快就上路了
These jokers will be gone soon.

193
00:19:02,059 --> 00:19:07,481
告诉我 为什么你们来我的镇子上惹麻烦?
Now, why y'all wanna come into my town and start trouble?

194
00:19:07,648 --> 00:19:10,901
还吓坏了这些老实人
And scare all these nice people.

195
00:19:12,069 --> 00:19:14,738
你们就没点正经事做吗?
You ain't got nothing better to do

196
00:19:14,905 --> 00:19:18,116
净来我比尔·夏普的小镇瞎捣乱
than to come into Bill Sharp's town

197
00:19:18,283 --> 00:19:20,536
简直是自取其辱
and show your ass?

198
00:19:28,877 --> 00:19:32,798
你把我们警长怎么了?
What'd you just do to our sheriff?

199
00:19:44,101 --> 00:19:46,436
你可以去叫司法官了
Now you can get the marshal.

200
00:19:47,938 --> 00:19:50,274
司法官! 司法官!
Marshal! Marshal!

201
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:52,693
- 我们要不要进去等?  - 咱们走吧?
- Should we wait inside?  - Can we just leave?

202
00:19:52,860 --> 00:19:54,069
你先请
After you.

203
00:19:56,530 --> 00:20:00,742
把路对面的马车横着停边上 对着那家酒馆
Move that buckboard a long ways across the street from the saloon.

204
00:20:00,909 --> 00:20:03,787
然后找六个人拿着来复枪蹲在车后面
I want six men, six rifles behind it.

205
00:20:03,954 --> 00:20:06,123
两个人拿着来复枪上这边房顶
I want two men, two rifles up on this roof.

206
00:20:06,290 --> 00:20:08,625
那边也上去两个
Two men, two rifles on that roof.

207
00:20:08,792 --> 00:20:11,753
所有枪都指着那扇大门
All the barrels aimed at that front door.

208
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:14,923
来人把可怜的比尔抬走
Somebody get poor Bill outta the goddamn street.

209
00:20:16,091 --> 00:20:18,260
酒吧里的歹徒你听着!
You in the saloon!

210
00:20:18,427 --> 00:20:21,763
你们已经被上百把来复枪包围了
We got a hundred rifles aimed at every way out of that buildin'.

211
00:20:22,472 --> 00:20:25,642
你们只有一次活着出来的机会
You got one chance to get out of this alive.

212
00:20:26,476 --> 00:20:28,979
你和你的黑鬼现在就弃械投降
You and your nigger come out right now with your hands over your head,

213
00:20:29,146 --> 00:20:31,106
就现在
and I mean right now.

214
00:20:32,232 --> 00:20:35,652
是司法官大人亲自来接见我吗?
Is this the marshal I have the pleasure of addressing?

215
00:20:35,819 --> 00:20:37,613
是的
Yes, it is.

216
00:20:37,779 --> 00:20:39,865
我是美国司法官吉尔·塔图姆
This is U.S. Marshal Gill Tatum.

217
00:20:40,032 --> 00:20:42,326
无上荣幸 司法官大人
Na wunderbar, marshal.

218
00:20:42,826 --> 00:20:46,413
我已经正如你说的
I have relieved myself of all weapons,

219
00:20:46,580 --> 00:20:49,499
卸去了所有武器
and just as you have instructed,

220
00:20:49,666 --> 00:20:52,336
我正在以投降的姿态
I am ready to step outside

221
00:20:52,502 --> 00:20:56,590
向外面走来
with my hands raised above my head.

222
00:20:57,674 --> 00:21:00,093
我相信我作为
I trust as a representative

223
00:21:00,260 --> 00:21:03,639
美利坚合众国刑事司法体系的代表
of the criminal justice system of the United States of America,

224
00:21:03,805 --> 00:21:09,645
在上法庭之前是不可以被你和你手下
I shan't be shot down in the street by either you or your deputies

225
00:21:09,811 --> 00:21:12,648
乱枪打死在大街上的
before I've had my day in court.

226
00:21:12,814 --> 00:21:15,150
你是说不可以像你对警长那样
You mean like you did our sheriff.

227
00:21:15,317 --> 00:21:17,110
像条狗似的死在马路中央
Shot him down like a dog in the street.

228
00:21:17,277 --> 00:21:19,613
对 我就是那个意思
Yes, that's exactly what I mean.

229
00:21:19,780 --> 00:21:25,452
你能以执法者的名义承诺 不把我像狗一样射杀在马路中央吗?
Do I have your word as a lawman not to shoot me down like a dog in the street?

230
00:21:28,789 --> 00:21:32,042
好吧 尽管我们都想把你格杀勿论
Well, much as we'd all enjoy seeing something like that,

231
00:21:32,209 --> 00:21:35,212
但我们还都是明察秋毫的
ain't nobody gonna cheat the hangman in my town.

232
00:21:36,254 --> 00:21:39,216
好的 司法官 我们出来了
Fair enough, marshal. Here we come.

233
00:21:41,051 --> 00:21:43,220
他们枪栓都拉得够紧的
They're a little tense out there.

234
00:21:43,387 --> 00:21:46,848
你就别乱来 让我来跟他们说
So don't make any quick movements, and let me do the talking.

235
00:21:47,182 --> 00:21:49,851
出来吧
Come ahead.

236
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:58,151
赤手空拳啦?
You unarmed?

237
00:21:58,318 --> 00:22:00,028
是 我们都缴械了
Yes, indeed we are.

238
00:22:00,779 --> 00:22:04,116
司法官塔图姆 我能不能向你和你的手下
Marshal Tatum, may I address you and your deputies,

239
00:22:04,282 --> 00:22:06,243
还有在这的整个多特里镇的村民
and apparently the entire town of Daughtrey,

240
00:22:06,410 --> 00:22:08,745
介绍刚刚发生的那场事故?
as to the incident that just occurred?

241
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:12,541
- 继续  - 多谢
- Go on.  - Thank you.

242
00:22:12,708 --> 00:22:14,835
我的名字是金·舒尔茨医生
My name is Dr. King Schultz.

243
00:22:15,002 --> 00:22:18,255
像你一样 司法官 我也是名执法人员
Like yourself, marshal, I'm a servant of the court.

244
00:22:18,422 --> 00:22:21,842
那黄土中的尸首 比尔·夏普
The man lying dead in the dirt, who the good people of Daughtrey

245
00:22:22,009 --> 00:22:26,096
这位多特里镇的平民选出的警长
saw fit to elect as their sheriff, who went by the name of Bill Sharp,

246
00:22:26,263 --> 00:22:30,851
实际上真名是威拉德·佩克 是个通缉犯
is actually a wanted outlaw by the name of Willard Peck,

247
00:22:31,018 --> 00:22:33,603
被悬赏200块
with a price on his head of $200.

248
00:22:33,770 --> 00:22:36,732
不论生死
Now that's $200, dead or alive.

249
00:22:36,898 --> 00:22:38,233
你说什么!
The hell, you say!

250
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:42,446
我也深知这是条令人不安的坏消息
I'm aware this is probably disconcerting news.

251
00:22:42,612 --> 00:22:45,782
我敢打赌这个人是在大概两年前
But I'm willing to wager this man was elected sheriff

252
00:22:45,949 --> 00:22:48,452
被选上当警长的?
sometime in the past two years?

253
00:22:49,369 --> 00:22:50,370
对
Yeah.

254
00:22:50,537 --> 00:22:53,957
我知道是因为这个人三年前 在德州卢博克市
I know this because three years ago, he was rustling cattle

255
00:22:54,124 --> 00:22:57,586
BC科里根畜牧公司犯下了偷牛大罪
from the B.C. Corrigan Cattle Company of Lubbock, Texas.

256
00:22:57,753 --> 00:23:01,548
现在 我手拿的是由德州奥斯汀
Now, this is a warrant made out by

257
00:23:01,715 --> 00:23:07,387
巡回法院亨利·亚伦·罗德缪法官签发的逮捕证
Circuit Court Judge Henry Allen Laudermilk of Austin, Texas.

258
00:23:07,554 --> 00:23:09,264
你可以给他发个电报
You're encouraged to wire him.

259
00:23:09,431 --> 00:23:14,478
他会证实我的说辞 揭开你已故的亲爱的警长的真面目
He'll back up who I am and who your dear departed sheriff was.

260
00:23:22,652 --> 00:23:26,573
换句话说 司法官大人 你欠我200块
In other words, marshal, you owe me $200.

261
00:23:35,248 --> 00:23:36,750
见鬼了
I'll be damned.

262
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:08,365
处理完布里托兄弟之后
After this Brittle business is behind us,

263
00:24:08,532 --> 00:24:14,079
你会得到自由 还有75块进账...
you'll be a free man, with a horse, $75 in your back pocket...

264
00:24:16,873 --> 00:24:18,291
之后你有什么打算?
What's your plan after that?

265
00:24:20,544 --> 00:24:24,381
找到我的妻子 赎回她的自由
Find my wife, and buy her freedom.

266
00:24:26,633 --> 00:24:31,513
姜戈 我还不知道你是已婚男士
Django, I had no idea you were a married man.

267
00:24:32,013 --> 00:24:34,307
大部分奴隶都信婚姻?
Do most slaves believe in marriage?

268
00:24:34,474 --> 00:24:38,061
反正我和我妻子信
Oh, me and my wife do.

269
00:24:38,228 --> 00:24:42,399
卡鲁肯老头不信 所以我们 呃... 跑了出来
Old Man Carrucan didn't. That's why we, uh... we run off.

270
00:24:43,608 --> 00:24:45,235
姜戈
Django.

271
00:24:45,902 --> 00:24:48,488
姜戈 姜戈
Django, Django.

272
00:24:48,655 --> 00:24:51,366
你胆子不小啊 姜戈
You got sand, Django.

273
00:24:52,075 --> 00:24:53,952
这个孩子胆子不小
Boy's got sand.

274
00:24:55,745 --> 00:24:58,874
我偏不喜欢有胆的黑鬼
I got no use for a nigger with sand.

275
00:25:00,584 --> 00:25:04,087
在他脸这儿烙个代表逃跑的r字
I want you to burn a runaway "r" right here on his cheek.

276
00:25:04,254 --> 00:25:05,297
那个女孩也烙上
And the girl, too.

277
00:25:07,424 --> 00:25:12,220
然后把他们带到格林维尔卖场上卖掉
And I want you to take 'em to the Greenville auction and sell 'em.

278
00:25:13,054 --> 00:25:14,931
两个都卖掉
Both of 'em.

279
00:25:15,098 --> 00:25:16,850
分开卖
Separately.

280
00:25:19,311 --> 00:25:20,645
这个嘛...
And this one...

281
00:25:23,273 --> 00:25:25,984
我要你贱卖
you will sell him cheap.

282
00:25:27,944 --> 00:25:29,446
在格林维尔...
In Greenville...

283
00:25:31,990 --> 00:25:34,951
应该有个档案库
there should be some sort of a records office.

284
00:25:42,167 --> 00:25:44,377
记录着她什么时候被卖掉的...
You know when she was sold...

285
00:25:45,837 --> 00:25:48,798
还有她从哪来
you know where she came from,

286
00:25:48,965 --> 00:25:50,800
以及她的名字
and you know her name.

287
00:25:51,593 --> 00:25:53,136
她叫什么来着?
What is her name?

288
00:25:53,303 --> 00:25:54,971
布隆希达
Broomhilda.

289
00:25:56,556 --> 00:25:59,809
- 什么?  - 布隆 希达
- What?  - Broom-hilda.

290
00:25:59,976 --> 00:26:01,937
- 布隆希达?  - 对的
- Broomhilda?  - Hm-mm.

291
00:26:04,022 --> 00:26:07,025
- 她的主人是德国人?  - 对 你怎么知道的?
- Were her owners German?  - Yeah, how you know?

292
00:26:07,901 --> 00:26:09,319
她不是在卡鲁肯农场出生的
She wasn't born on the Carrucan plantation.

293
00:26:09,486 --> 00:26:12,030
她被德国女主人养大 沙夫特家
She was raised by a German mistress, the Von Shafts.

294
00:26:12,197 --> 00:26:14,324
她也会说一点德语
She speak a little German, too.

295
00:26:14,491 --> 00:26:16,243
- 你妻子?  - 嗯
- Your wife?  - Hm-mm.

296
00:26:16,409 --> 00:26:18,245
她还小的时候 女主人教过她
When she was little, her mistress taught her so she'd have somebody

297
00:26:18,411 --> 00:26:19,996
为了能有个人说说话
to speak German with.

298
00:26:21,581 --> 00:26:24,167
好了 我来理一遍
Well, let me get this straight.

299
00:26:24,334 --> 00:26:28,922
你的奴隶妻子会说德语 而且她叫布隆希达·沙夫特?
Your slave wife speaks German and her name is Broomhilda Von Shaft?

300
00:26:29,089 --> 00:26:30,215
对
Yep.

301
00:26:34,261 --> 00:26:37,013
他们叫我希达
They call me Hildi.

302
00:26:49,261 --> 00:26:51,013
田纳西州

303
00:26:53,697 --> 00:26:59,286
进这些农场之后 我们要演场戏
When we gain access to these plantations, we'll be putting on an act.

304
00:27:00,620 --> 00:27:03,373
你有自己的角色要扮演
You'll be playing a character.

305
00:27:10,255 --> 00:27:11,381
怎么样?
Hm?

306
00:27:12,090 --> 00:27:13,508
不好看啊?
No?

307
00:27:20,515 --> 00:27:24,978
表演的时候 你不能出戏
During the act, you can never break character.

308
00:27:26,062 --> 00:27:27,605
你明白么?
Do you understand?

309
00:27:28,356 --> 00:27:30,900
嗯 不出戏
Yeah. Don't break character.

310
00:27:33,236 --> 00:27:37,157
你的角色就是随从
And your character is that of The Valet.

311
00:27:37,907 --> 00:27:39,409
什么意思?
What that is?

312
00:27:40,327 --> 00:27:42,704
说不好听的就是仆人
That's a fancy word for servant.

313
00:27:42,871 --> 00:27:44,122
- 随从?  - 嗯
- Valet?  - Hm-mm.

314
00:27:45,623 --> 00:27:50,128
现在嘛 姜戈 你可以为你的角色选戏服了
And now, Django, you may choose your character's costume.

315
00:27:52,547 --> 00:27:54,382
你让我给我自己选衣服?
Youse gonna let me pick out my own clothes?

316
00:27:54,549 --> 00:27:55,508
那是自然
But of course.

317
00:28:24,287 --> 00:28:25,497
吁
Whoa.

318
00:28:29,793 --> 00:28:33,380
在这里黑鬼骑马是犯法的
It's against the law for niggers to ride horses in this territory.

319
00:28:33,546 --> 00:28:36,925
他是我的随从 他不走路的
This is my valet. My valet does not walk.

320
00:28:37,092 --> 00:28:40,970
- 我是说在马上的这黑鬼...  - 他的名字是姜戈
- I said niggers on horses...  - His name is Django.

321
00:28:41,137 --> 00:28:43,932
他是自由的 他想骑什么就骑什么
He's a free man. He can ride what he pleases.

322
00:28:44,099 --> 00:28:47,560
在我的地盘可不行 至少在我的黑鬼面前 不行
Not on my property. Not around my niggers, he can't.

323
00:28:48,228 --> 00:28:53,233
这位先生 我想我们误会了
My good sir, perhaps we got off on the wrong boot.

324
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:55,860
请容我解释
Allow me to unring this bell.

325
00:28:56,027 --> 00:28:59,864
我是金·舒尔茨医生 这是我的随从姜戈
My name is Dr. King Schultz. This is my valet, Django.

326
00:29:00,031 --> 00:29:02,158
这是我们的坐骑托尼和小德
And these are our horses, Tony and Fritz.

327
00:29:05,995 --> 00:29:07,372
班尼特先生?
Mr. Bennett?

328
00:29:07,539 --> 00:29:11,751
我听说您是一位绅士 也是位生意人
I've been led to believe that you are a gentleman and a businessman.

329
00:29:11,918 --> 00:29:15,880
因此我们才骑马从德州来到了田纳西州
And it is for these attributes we've ridden from Texas to Tennessee

330
00:29:16,047 --> 00:29:17,966
与您会面
to parley with you now.

331
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:23,096
我想从你这里买一个女奴
I wish to purchase one of your nigger gals.

332
00:29:24,639 --> 00:29:27,725
你和你的小喽啰从德州来到田纳西
You and your Jimmie rode from Texas to Tennessee

333
00:29:27,892 --> 00:29:29,686
就是为了买我一个女奴?
to buy one of my nigger gals?

334
00:29:29,853 --> 00:29:31,521
不事先打个招呼 啥也没有就来了?
No appointment, no nothin'?

335
00:29:31,688 --> 00:29:33,606
噢 的确如此
Oh, I'm afraid so.

336
00:29:33,773 --> 00:29:36,192
嗯 那如果我说我不喜欢你呢?
Well, what if I was to say I don't like you?

337
00:29:36,359 --> 00:29:38,027
还有你的小丑黑鬼?
Or your fancy-pants nigger?

338
00:29:38,194 --> 00:29:40,405
我什么都不打算卖给你
And I wouldn't sell you a tinker's damn.

339
00:29:40,572 --> 00:29:42,532
你想说什么吗?
Now what you got to say about that?

340
00:29:45,869 --> 00:29:47,787
班尼特先生
Mr. Bennett.

341
00:29:47,954 --> 00:29:51,207
如果您真如传闻中说的那样具有商业头脑的话
