00:42:59,119 --> 00:43:02,081
没人带着多余的口袋!
No, nobody brought an extra bag!

501
00:43:02,248 --> 00:43:03,874
我就想问问
I'm just askin'.

502
00:43:04,041 --> 00:43:05,834
骑马的时候一定要戴吗?
Do we have to wear 'em when we ride?

503
00:43:06,001 --> 00:43:07,211
废话!
Oh, well, shitfire!

504
00:43:07,378 --> 00:43:10,464
骑马的时候不戴还有什么意义!
If you don't wear 'em as you ride up, that just defeats the purpose!

505
00:43:10,631 --> 00:43:12,591
问题是戴着这个我什么都看不到!
Well, I can't see in this fuckin' thing!

506
00:43:12,758 --> 00:43:15,469
戴着这玩意我喘不过气啊 我不能戴着它骑马!
I can't breathe in this fuckin' thing and I can't ride in this fuckin' thing!

507
00:43:15,636 --> 00:43:18,055
谁管你们! 我要回家了!
Well, fuck all y'all! I'm goin' home!

508
00:43:18,222 --> 00:43:22,017
我老婆忙了一整天做了30个口袋
Now, I watched my wife work all day gettin' 30 bags together

509
00:43:22,184 --> 00:43:24,186
给你们这些不感恩的杂种
for you ungrateful sons-a-bitches,

510
00:43:24,353 --> 00:43:28,107
我听到除了抱怨就是抱怨还有抱怨!
and all I can hear is criticize, criticize, criticize!

511
00:43:28,274 --> 00:43:31,443
从今往后 别指望我帮你们办事了!
From now on, don't ask me or mine for nothin'!

512
00:43:32,736 --> 00:43:35,614
听着 别忘了我们是来干嘛的
Now, look, let's not forget why we're here.

513
00:43:35,781 --> 00:43:38,867
山那边有个黑鬼杀手呢!
We got a killer nigger over that hill there!

514
00:43:39,034 --> 00:43:40,369
我们要给他点颜色看看
And we gotta make a lesson out of him.

515
00:43:40,536 --> 00:43:44,373
好吧 我有点乱 到底罩不罩口袋?
OK, I'm confused. Are the bags on or off?

516
00:43:44,540 --> 00:43:49,336
我们不是一致认为罩口袋是好主意吗?
I think we all think the bag was a nice idea.

517
00:43:49,503 --> 00:43:50,462
好吧
Yeah.

518
00:43:50,629 --> 00:43:54,717
不过 没有特指谁啊 这手艺可真不怎么样
But, not pointin' any fingers, they coulda been done better.

519
00:43:55,676 --> 00:43:59,388
那这次不戴可以吗
So how 'bout no bags this time,

520
00:43:59,555 --> 00:44:04,560
下次我们改良一下 再戴怎么样
but next time we do the bags right and then we go full regalia.

521
00:44:04,727 --> 00:44:06,729
- 这主意我喜欢  - 投你一票 罗伯特
- I like that idea a lot.  - You get my vote, Robert.

522
00:44:06,895 --> 00:44:10,232
等等 我没说不罩口袋
Wait a minute! I didn't say no bags.

523
00:44:10,399 --> 00:44:12,401
但是大家都看不见啊
But nobody can see.

524
00:44:12,568 --> 00:44:13,652
那又怎么了?
So?

525
00:44:13,819 --> 00:44:15,696
看得见比较好吧
So it'd be nice to see.

526
00:44:15,863 --> 00:44:20,617
该死的! 我们是突袭! 我看不到 你也看到不到!
Goddamn it! This is a raid! I can't see, you can't see!

527
00:44:20,784 --> 00:44:26,165
那又怎么了? 该死的马能看到不就得了! 突袭吗不是!
So what? All that matters is can the fuckin' horse see! That's a raid!

528
00:44:29,918 --> 00:44:31,628
根本看不清!
I can't see shit!

529
00:44:31,795 --> 00:44:35,424
他在这! 从车厢下面把那黑鬼拖出来!
There he is! Get that nigger out from under that wagon!

530
00:44:36,258 --> 00:44:38,260
从车里把黑鬼爱好者也弄出来!
And get that nigger-lover outta the wagon!

531
00:44:38,427 --> 00:44:40,054
黑鬼不在这里 老爹!
That nigger ain't down here, Big Daddy!

532
00:44:40,220 --> 00:44:41,638
- 什么?  - 他们耍了我们!
- What?  - They tricked us!

533
00:44:41,805 --> 00:44:42,848
那 那他们在哪?
Well, where are they?

534
00:44:43,015 --> 00:44:44,433
再会
Auf Wiedersehen.

535
00:44:50,147 --> 00:44:51,940
噢!
Oh!

536
00:44:52,107 --> 00:44:53,150
十环
Bull's-eye.

537
00:44:56,153 --> 00:44:59,448
他们逃跑了
Look at 'em run.

538
00:45:02,076 --> 00:45:04,661
一群懦夫就是这样
Yeah, cowards tend to do that.

539
00:45:04,828 --> 00:45:06,789
该死的!
Goddamn it!

540
00:45:12,920 --> 00:45:14,171
该死的!
Goddamn it!

541
00:45:18,801 --> 00:45:20,511
你来试试?
Would you care to?

542
00:45:27,309 --> 00:45:29,144
罩着这玩意什么都看不到!
Can't see shit outta this!

543
00:45:29,770 --> 00:45:31,939
- 他要逃了  - 我瞄到了
- He's getting away.  - I got him.

544
00:45:33,982 --> 00:45:35,442
老爹要逃了
Big Daddy's getting away.

545
00:45:35,609 --> 00:45:36,860
我瞄准了
I got him.

546
00:45:52,126 --> 00:45:53,168
干掉他了
Got him.

547
00:45:58,006 --> 00:46:01,009
很有天赋啊
The kid's a natural.

548
00:46:11,687 --> 00:46:15,482
你怎么知道布隆希达的第一个主人是德国人?
How you know Broomhilda's first masters was German?

549
00:46:15,649 --> 00:46:17,901
布隆希达是个德国名字
Broomhilda is a German name.

550
00:46:18,068 --> 00:46:20,779
既然给她起这个名字 他们应该是德国人
If they named her, it stands to reason they'd be German.

551
00:46:20,946 --> 00:46:23,198
你们那里很多女孩都叫布隆希达吗?
Lots of gals where you're from named Broomhilda?

552
00:46:23,991 --> 00:46:26,952
布隆希达在德国是一个家喻户晓的名字
Broomhilda is the name of a character

553
00:46:27,119 --> 00:46:31,039
她是一个德国传说中的人物
in the most popular of all the German legends.

554
00:46:31,206 --> 00:46:33,167
布隆希达还有个故事?
There's a story about Broomhilda?

555
00:46:33,333 --> 00:46:35,043
是的 有个故事
Oh, yes, there is.

556
00:46:41,091 --> 00:46:44,553
- 你知道这故事?  - 每个德国人都知道
- Do you know it?  - Oh, every German knows that story.

557
00:46:50,976 --> 00:46:52,352
想让我给你讲讲?
Would you like me to tell you?

558
00:46:53,854 --> 00:46:59,860
嗯 布隆希达是个公主
Well, Broomhilda was a princess.

559
00:47:01,695 --> 00:47:05,782
她是万神之神沃坦的女儿
She was a daughter of Wotan, god of all gods.

560
00:47:06,825 --> 00:47:10,037
不过 她父亲对她很恼火
Anyway, her father is really mad at her.

561
00:47:10,204 --> 00:47:11,455
她干什么了?
What she do?

562
00:47:12,414 --> 00:47:13,874
记不清了
I can't exactly remember.

563
00:47:14,041 --> 00:47:16,710
反正就是违抗了他父亲的命令
She disobeys him in some way.

564
00:47:16,877 --> 00:47:20,047
所以他把关在一座山的山顶
So he puts her on top of the mountain.

565
00:47:20,714 --> 00:47:21,840
布隆希达在山里?
Broomhilda's on a mountain?

566
00:47:22,007 --> 00:47:23,258
这是德国传说
It's a German legend,

567
00:47:23,425 --> 00:47:26,220
总是有个山什么的
there's always going to be a mountain in there somewhere.

568
00:47:26,386 --> 00:47:30,432
他还安排了喷火龙守卫那座山
And he puts a fire-breathing dragon there to guard the mountain.

569
00:47:32,100 --> 00:47:37,189
用地狱之火围绕着她
And he surrounds her in a circle of hellfire.

570
00:47:38,649 --> 00:47:42,986
因此 布隆希达只好那么待着
And there, Broomhilda shall remain.

571
00:47:44,279 --> 00:47:49,576
除非有一位勇士能来拯救她
Unless a hero arises brave enough to save her.

572
00:47:50,661 --> 00:47:52,246
有么?
Does a fella arise?

573
00:47:52,412 --> 00:47:55,374
有啊 姜戈 实际上 他真的去了
Yes, Django, as a matter of fact, he does.

574
00:47:55,541 --> 00:47:57,584
一个叫齐格弗里德的小伙子
A fella named Siegfried.

575
00:47:58,293 --> 00:47:59,294
齐格弗里德救到她了吗?
Does Siegfried save her?

576
00:48:01,463 --> 00:48:04,091
他做到了 很了不起
Quite spectacularly so.

577
00:48:05,133 --> 00:48:09,263
他爬上了大山 因为他无所畏惧
He scales the mountain, because he's not afraid of it.

578
00:48:09,972 --> 00:48:14,142
他杀死了恶龙 因为他无所畏惧
He slays the dragon, because he's not afraid of him.

579
00:48:14,309 --> 00:48:16,812
他穿越了地狱之火...
And he walks through hellfire...

580
00:48:19,147 --> 00:48:21,525
因为布隆希达值得这么做
because Broomhilda's worth it.

581
00:48:25,654 --> 00:48:27,322
我了解他的感觉
I know how he feel.

582
00:48:28,782 --> 00:48:31,660
我觉得我刚刚才了解到
I think I'm just starting to realize that.

583
00:48:37,165 --> 00:48:41,336
嗯 听着 姜戈...
Now, look, Django...

584
00:48:44,256 --> 00:48:48,302
我毫不怀疑你会去拯救你的爱人...
I don't doubt that one day you'll save your lady love...

585
00:48:49,428 --> 00:48:53,015
但我从心里不希望你去格林维尔
but I can't let you go to Greenville in a good conscience.

586
00:48:54,057 --> 00:48:58,520
密西西比的奴隶市场可不适合你啊
A slave auction town in Mississippi isn't the place for you to visit.

587
00:48:58,687 --> 00:49:01,565
不论你是不是自由人 那都很危险
Free or not, it's just too dangerous.

588
00:49:04,526 --> 00:49:06,695
让我来问你一个问题
But let me ask you a question.

589
00:49:14,202 --> 00:49:16,622
你喜欢当赏金猎人吗?
How do you like the bounty hunting business?

590
00:49:18,123 --> 00:49:20,459
杀白人还有钱拿?
Kill white folks and they pay you for it?

591
00:49:21,293 --> 00:49:22,628
怎么会不喜欢?
What's not to like?

592
00:49:22,794 --> 00:49:25,213
我得承认 我俩搭档很不错
Now, I have to admit, we make a good team.

593
00:49:25,380 --> 00:49:28,216
我以为我杀了大约翰和小罗让你很不高兴呢
I thought you was mad at me for killin' Big John and Lil Raj.

594
00:49:28,383 --> 00:49:30,469
没错 那种场合下你是有点过分了
Yeah, on that occasion you were a tad overzealous,

595
00:49:30,636 --> 00:49:32,596
不过一般来说 那也没什么
but normally, that's a good thing.

596
00:49:33,388 --> 00:49:35,599
我们搭伙干一个冬天怎么样?
How'd you like to partner up for the winter?

597
00:49:35,766 --> 00:49:37,768
搭伙是什么意思?
What you mean "partner up"?

598
00:49:37,934 --> 00:49:42,230
整个冬天直到冰雪融化你跟着我...
You work with me through the winter till the snow melts...

599
00:49:43,231 --> 00:49:45,233
奖金我分你三分之一
I give you a third of my bounties.

600
00:49:46,443 --> 00:49:50,364
我们这个冬天赚些钱 等雪化了
So we make some money this winter, and when the snow melts,

601
00:49:50,530 --> 00:49:53,450
我亲自带你去格林维尔
I'll take you to Greenville myself

602
00:49:53,617 --> 00:49:56,828
我们去找你妻子的下落
and we'll find where they sent your wife.

603
00:50:01,083 --> 00:50:02,834
你为什么这么关心我?
Why you care what happen to me?

604
00:50:04,586 --> 00:50:06,546
为什么关心我是否找得到妻子?
Why you care if I find my wife?

605
00:50:06,713 --> 00:50:08,090
坦白说...
Frankly...

606
00:50:09,383 --> 00:50:12,260
我从没有给过谁自由之身
I've never given anybody their freedom before.

607
00:50:12,427 --> 00:50:16,264
现在我给了你自由 我觉得我对你负有一定的责任
And now that I have, I feel vaguely responsible for you.

608
00:50:17,516 --> 00:50:21,228
再说 一个德国人遇到了现实中的齐格弗里德 没理由不帮一把的
Plus, when a German meets a real life Siegfried, that's kind of a big deal.

609
00:50:23,772 --> 00:50:26,650
作为一个德国人 我有义务帮你
As a German, I'm obliged to help you on your quest

610
00:50:26,817 --> 00:50:29,444
拯救你的爱人布隆希达
to rescue your beloved Broomhilda.

611
00:52:38,740 --> 00:52:39,741
注意点
You got her.

612
00:52:46,540 --> 00:52:51,461
哦 杀白人挣钱先生 你怎么了?
Ooh. What happened to Mr. "I Wanna Shoot White Folks For Money"?

613
00:52:51,628 --> 00:52:54,339
- 他儿子也在那  - 嗯 很好
- His son's with him.  - Well, good.

614
00:52:54,506 --> 00:52:56,091
他有个挚爱亲人在身边
He'll have a loved one with him.

615
00:52:56,258 --> 00:52:58,760
也许还能留句遗言
Maybe even share a last word.

616
00:53:00,762 --> 00:53:02,806
比其他人强多了
That's better than most of them get.

617
00:53:02,973 --> 00:53:05,267
坏人不应该有这种好报
Damn sight better than he deserves.

618
00:53:13,441 --> 00:53:14,776
枪放下吧
Put down the rifle.

619
00:53:17,779 --> 00:53:19,489
别怕 我没生你的气
Don't worry, I'm not mad at you.

620
00:53:20,282 --> 00:53:22,617
我们拿出斯密·巴考尔的通缉令
Let's take out Smitty Bacall's handbill.

621
00:53:26,580 --> 00:53:28,081
大声读出来
Read it aloud.

622
00:53:28,957 --> 00:53:30,750
就当是今天的功课
Consider that today's lesson.

623
00:53:33,169 --> 00:53:35,839
通缉 无论死活
Wanted. Dead or alive.

624
00:53:36,798 --> 00:53:40,719
斯密·巴考尔以及斯密·巴考尔的
Smitty Bacall and the Smitty Bacall

625
00:53:40,886 --> 00:53:43,138
- 团伙  - 团伙
- Gang.  - Gang.

626
00:53:43,305 --> 00:53:46,975
因谋杀以及打劫...
For murder and stagecoach...

627
00:53:48,393 --> 00:53:49,936
驿站马车
robbery.

628
00:53:50,103 --> 00:53:52,898
- 七 零 零 零...  - 七千
- Seven-zero-zero-zero...  - Seven thousand.

629
00:53:53,064 --> 00:53:54,399
千
Thousand.

630
00:53:54,566 --> 00:53:58,778
悬赏七千美元捉拿斯密·巴考尔
$7,000 for Smitty Bacall.

631
00:53:58,945 --> 00:54:04,034
一千五百美元捉拿他的每个...
$1,500 for each of his...

632
00:54:04,200 --> 00:54:05,994
团伙...
gang...

633
00:54:07,037 --> 00:54:09,039
- 成...  - 成员
- Mem...  - Members.

634
00:54:09,748 --> 00:54:14,377
已知的斯密·巴考尔团伙成员于下:
Known members of the Smitty Bacall Gang are as follas:

635
00:54:14,544 --> 00:54:16,296
- 如下  - 如下
- Follows.  - Follows.

636
00:54:16,463 --> 00:54:20,175
丹迪·迈克尔斯 杰拉尔德·纳什和...
Dandy Michaels, Gerald Nash and...

637
00:54:21,301 --> 00:54:23,219
疯子克雷格·昆斯
Crazy Craig Koons.

638
00:54:24,220 --> 00:54:26,473
这才是斯密·巴考尔的真面目
That is who Smitty Bacall is.

639
00:54:26,640 --> 00:54:29,517
他要是22岁开始老实经营农场
If Smitty Bacall wanted to start a farm at 22,

640
00:54:29,684 --> 00:54:31,645
就不会被印在这上面了
they would never have printed that.

641
00:54:32,354 --> 00:54:35,774
可斯密·巴考尔想抢劫马车
But Smitty Bacall wanted to rob stagecoaches

642
00:54:35,941 --> 00:54:38,360
为达目的他不惜杀人
and he didn't mind killing people to do it.

643
00:54:39,027 --> 00:54:42,364
你想做我的工作来挣钱救你妻子吗?
Do you want to save your wife by doing what I do?

644
00:54:43,615 --> 00:54:45,075
这就是我的工作
This is what I do.

645
00:54:45,241 --> 00:54:48,787
我杀人 用尸体换赏金
I kill people and sell their corpses for cash.

646
00:54:49,704 --> 00:54:53,500
这具尸体值七千美元
This corpse is worth $7,000.

647
00:54:53,667 --> 00:54:55,877
别婆婆妈妈了 朝他开枪
Now quit your pussyfooting and shoot him.

648
00:55:06,012 --> 00:55:07,389
爸爸?
Pa?

649
00:55:07,555 --> 00:55:08,890
爸爸!
Pa!

650
00:55:17,357 --> 00:55:19,067
拿着
Here.

651
00:55:19,234 --> 00:55:21,319
你得保管好这斯密·巴考尔的通缉令
You need to keep this Smitty Bacall handbill.

652
00:55:21,486 --> 00:55:23,571
- 为什么?  - 这是好运气
- Why?  - It's good luck.

653
00:55:23,738 --> 00:55:26,533
要保存好第一份赏金通缉令
You always keep the handbill of your first bounty.

654
00:56:14,456 --> 00:56:15,874
非常准
That's accurate.

655
00:57:24,192 --> 00:57:27,320
医生 姜戈 你们好啊?
Doctor, Django, how the hell are ya?

656
00:57:28,363 --> 00:57:30,532
那些又是谁啊?
Who the hell-a you got there?

657
00:57:30,698 --> 00:57:32,659
威尔逊劳团伙
The Wilson-Lowe Gang.

658
00:57:32,826 --> 00:57:35,829
什么威尔逊劳团伙?
Who the hell is the Wilson-Lowe Gang?

659
00:57:36,538 --> 00:57:41,084
坏蛋查克·威尔逊 更坏的鲍比·劳和三个随从
Bad Chuck Wilson and meaner Bobby Lowe and three of their acolytes.

660
00:57:41,251 --> 00:57:44,879
哦 就放这儿吧 他们也跑不了了
Huh. Well, just leave 'em out here, they ain't going nowhere.

661
00:57:45,046 --> 00:57:47,423
你们别在雪里待着 进屋来
Why don't you come in then out of the snowy snow

662
00:57:47,590 --> 00:57:49,425
喝点咖啡
and get yourselves some coffee.

663
00:57:49,592 --> 00:57:52,137
昨天有人过生日 剩了点蛋糕
We had a birthday yesterday. Got some cake.

664
00:57:52,303 --> 00:57:53,721
